			<i>Gosh, she looks good all the time, </i>Bryn thought in amazement
			<i>, sick, with or without make-up, and when she first wakes up. Some people have all the luck.</i>
		</p>
		<p>Alex was at that moment looking at Bryn and thinking how adorable
			<i>she</i> looked with her tousled gold hair, sparkling green eyes, and soft clear complexion. Especially in her over-sized Atlanta Braves tee shirt. Not only was she cute, she was unbelievably sweet and kind. Alex loved the way the young nurse cuddled her patients after every frightening or painful procedure. Anytime they were in need of a hug or a story, she was always there to provide it for them. Alex had begun to request that Bryn be assigned to care for all her patients post operatively.
		</p>
		<p>While Bryn made breakfast, Alex showered and changed into a faded pair of jeans and a long sleeved, snug fitting, white v-neck tee. Her slender feet were bare as usual.</p>
		<p>A short while later, the two women sat down to breakfast in Alex's neat blue and white kitchen. Bryn had prepared coffee, fluffy scrambled eggs with cheese, bacon, and toasted English muffins.</p>
